ENTRY       EC 3.9.1.1                  Enzyme
NAME        phosphoamidase;
            creatine phosphatase
CLASS       Hydrolases;
            Acting on phosphorus-nitrogen bonds;
            Acting on phosphorus-nitrogen bonds (only sub-subclass identified to date)
SYSNAME     phosphamide hydrolase
REACTION    N-phosphocreatine + H2O = creatine + phosphate [RN:R01882]
ALL_REAC    R01882
SUBSTRATE   N-phosphocreatine [CPD:C02305];
            H2O [CPD:C00001]
PRODUCT     creatine [CPD:C00300];
            phosphate [CPD:C00009]
COMMENT     Also acts on N-phospho-arginine and other phosphoamides. Possibly identical with EC 3.1.3.9 (glucose-6-phosphatase) or EC 3.1.3.16 (protein-serine/threonine phosphatase).
